## Core Architecture Concept

### 1. Offline First with Dexie (IndexedDB)
- Free; user data is saved locally when offline.
- All data is initially stored on the client side.

### 2. Online Sync to Google Sheets
- Directly serves as a report and statistics dashboard.
- Sheets API free quota is sufficient for normal competition use.
- Batch writes can be used to reduce API request frequency.

### 3. ML / Analytics → Backend Pulls Data as Needed
- No need to write data in real-time to cloud Firestore.
- Periodically export data from Google Sheets to Node.js / Python / Cloud Functions.
- ML training or predictions can be performed on the backend.
- Sheets provides historical data for free, saving Firestore credits.

### 4. Optional Caching / Batch Processing
- For partial real-time functionality, deploy a lightweight Node.js API.
- The API only pulls data in batches when users are online or sends predictions.
- Avoids full real-time Firestore usage and high costs.

